1 Create or check if you alaready have one SSH key in your linux system
https://docs.github.com/es/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/checking-for-existing-ssh-keys

ls -la ~/.ssh

in the outcome identify the file .pub corresponding with your public key.


Then copy the key in your keyboard from this outcome

cat ~/.ssh/id_yourSSH.pub


Adding your ssh publick key in your github account.
https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/adding-a-new-ssh-key-to-your-github-account

From your git Account on the right top Profile / Setting / SSH and GPG keys / New SSH key paste your Public ssh key.
Check your connection from your linux konsole 

$>> ssh -T git@github.com

check that the digital finger print from the outcome shwon is one of the ownded by github and press (yes)
https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure/githubs-ssh-key-fingerprints

a sucessful connection will show the following message

> Hi username! You've successfully authenticated, but GitHub does not
> provide shell access.
